css:
/*
    The Chromium developers decided to make in-browser underlines (links, for example)
    skip descenders and other marks underneath the baseline by default.

    Unfortunately, they didn't include a setting for the user to override it.

    The best you can do is override that setting for all sites, even those that may
    be using it on purpose.
*/
html, body {
    text-decoration-skip-ink: none !important;
}
